      </table>
      <br>
      <p>To put it simply, the resolution of digital audio can be measured using two values - sample rate and bit-depth.</p>
      <p>The higher the sample rate and/or bit-depth, the higher audio resolution and the more digital information is being used to produce the audio.</p>
      <p><img src="images/high-res.jpg" width="100%" ></p>
    </div>
