          <td class="compatible">RX-V775</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V1075</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V2073</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V3073</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <br>
      <p>Similar to app control, Web Browser Control offers control over most functions of the AV receiver, though this time via a web interface.</p>
      <p>This means you can operate the receiver from a laptop or computer as well as a tablet or smart phone. The difference being that the operation is through a web browser, such as Internet Explorer, rather than an app.</p>
      <p><img src="images/web-browser.jpg" width="100%" ></p>
    </div>
    <h4 class="myheadings">Web Back-up &gt;&gt;</h4>
    <div class="thecontent">
      <table border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="10" width="100%">
        <tr>
          <td class="incompatible">RX-V375</td>
          <td class="incompatible">RX-V475</td>
          <td class="incompatible">RX-V500D</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="incompatible">RX-V575</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V675</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V775</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V1075</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V2073</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V3073</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <br>
      <p>Setting up a receiver can involve adjustment of many intricate settings including speaker calibration and re-assignment of inputs. Should the receiver fault or lose power due to a blackout, there’s a risk of losing this information and having to start again.</p>
      <p>The Web Back-Up function enables the user to save all the adjustments and load them back into their receiver as required, restoring all the previously saved settings.</p>
      <p><img src="images/web-backup.jpg" width="100%" ></p>
